  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Primary School Teacher",
  "description": "<p>Neurobix Method is a structured brain-training and learning system that integrates <strong>memory techniques, thinking skills, and Primary School academic subjects</strong>.<br />Our goal is to help students learn <strong>smarter, faster, and with confidence</strong>, not just score marks through rote memorisation.</p><p>We are looking for a <strong>Primary School Teacher / Tutor</strong> who is familiar with <strong>Singapore MOE syllabus</strong>, especially <strong>Science, English, and Mathematics</strong>, and is open to applying <strong>Neurobix Method</strong> in teaching.</p><h2>🎯 Key Responsibilities</h2><h3>🧑‍🏫 Academic Teaching (Primary Level)</h3><ul><li><p>Teach Primary School students (P1–P6) using <strong>Neurobix Method</strong></p></li><li><p>Subjects include:</p><ul><li><p><strong>Primary Science</strong> (key focus)</p></li><li><p><strong>Primary English</strong></p></li><li><p><strong>Primary Mathematics</strong></p></li></ul></li><li><p>Deliver structured lessons aligned with MOE syllabus while applying:</p><ul><li><p>Memory techniques</p></li><li><p>Thinking frameworks</p></li><li><p>Clear learning structures</p></li></ul></li></ul><h3>🧠 Neurobix Method Implementation</h3><ul><li><p>Apply Neurobix learning strategies such as:</p><ul><li><p>Memory techniques for content retention</p></li><li><p>Structured thinking for answering questions</p></li><li><p>Concept linking and visualisation</p></li></ul></li><li><p>Guide students to:</p><ul><li><p>Understand concepts</p></li><li><p>Organise information</p></li><li><p>Recall accurately during tests</p></li></ul></li></ul><h3>📚 Lesson Preparation & Assessment</h3><ul><li><p>Prepare lesson plans, worksheets, and simple assessments</p></li><li><p>Adapt teaching materials based on students’ levels and progress</p></li><li><p>Track students’ learning and improvement</p></li></ul><h3>🤝 Student & Parent Communication</h3><ul><li><p>Provide feedback on students’ learning progress</p></li><li><p>Support parent communication when required</p></li><li><p>Work with academic team to refine teaching approach</p></li></ul><h2>🧠 Requirements</h2><h3>✅ Must-Have</h3><ul><li><p>Familiar with <strong>Singapore Primary MOE syllabus</strong></p></li><li><p>Strong foundation in <strong>Primary Science, English, and/or Mathematics</strong></p></li><li><p>Teaching or tutoring experience with Primary students</p></li><li><p>Clear spoken and written English</p></li><li><p>Willing to learn and apply <strong>Neurobix Method</strong></p></li></ul><h3>👍 Nice-to-Have</h3><ul><li><p>Teaching qualification (NIE / PGDE / Diploma in Education)</p></li><li><p>Experience teaching <strong>PSLE Science</strong></p></li><li><p>Exposure to enrichment or learning skills programmes</p></li><li><p>Familiarity with memory techniques or thinking skills (training provided)</p></li></ul><h2>💡 Personality Fit </h2><ul><li><p>Open-minded and coachable</p></li><li><p>Patient and student-focused</p></li><li><p>Believes in <strong>learning how to learn</strong>, not rote drilling</p></li><li><p>Enjoys structured systems and continuous improvement</p></li></ul><h2>⏰ Working Arrangement</h2><ul><li><p>Weekday afternoons / evenings and/or weekends</p></li><li><p>Full-time or part-time options available</p></li><li><p><strong>Neurobix Method training provided</strong></p></li></ul><h2>💰 Salary & Growth</h2><ul><li><p>Competitive salary</p></li><li><p>Performance-based incentives</p></li><li><p>Clear growth pathway:</p><ul><li><p>Neurobix Certified Teacher</p></li><li><p>Subject Lead</p></li><li><p>Curriculum Development / Trainer</p></li></ul></li></ul>",
